title: Getting Started
text: refinebioc package collection functions can used refine Bioconductor objects. package designed used conjunction BiocFileCache package, provides way cache Bioconductor objects disk. refinebioc package provides functions refine cached objects, filtering, normalizing, transforming data.

title: Getting Started
text: experiment_listing function can used list available experiments. get feel data, can look first rows data frame. experiments variable contains data frame. Standard dplyr functions can used filter sort data frame. rb_get_experiment function loads experiment data memory. refine.bio website API, data loaded, prepares data asynchronously, function wait data ready, often taking minutes. interrupt function running. expts variable contains list SummarizedExperiment objects. view sample information, use colData function.

title: Getting Started
Getting Started
text: experiment_listing function can used list available experiments. get feel data, can look first rows data frame. experiments variable contains data frame. Standard dplyr functions can used filter sort data frame.

title: Getting Started

code: # load the SummarizedExperiment package # We'll need it later. suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(SummarizedExperiment))  # use an example datastore datastore_path <- datastore_example_path()  # Get the first dataset from the datastore example_dataset <- datastore_datasets(datastore_path)[1]  # Get the path to the dataset example_dataset_path <- file.path(datastore_path, example_dataset)  # Load the dataset example_se_list <- extract_local_dataset(example_dataset_path)  # Get the first experiment example_se <- example_se_list[[1]]  example_se #> class: SummarizedExperiment  #> dim: 19 48  #> metadata(13): accession_code description ... technology title #> assays(1): exprs #> rownames: NULL #> rowData names(1): Gene #> colnames(48): SRR6413028 SRR6413029 ... SRR6413074 SRR6413075 #> colData names(24): refinebio_accession_code experiment_accession ... #>   refinebio_title refinebio_treatment  # Get the first experiment's metadata str(metadata(example_se)) #> List of 13 #>  $ accession_code        : chr "SRP127409" #>  $ description           : chr "RNA was purified cancer cell lines. text: tibble tibble experiments refine.bio. tibble contains following columns: id: ID experiment title: title experiment publication_title: title publication associated experiment description: description experiment accession_code: accession code experiment alternate_accession_code: alternate accession code experiment technology: technology used generate data experiment submitter_institution: institution submitted experiment has_publication: Whether experiment publication associated publication_doi: DOI publication associated experiment publication_authors: authors publication associated experiment pubmed_id: PubMed ID publication associated experiment source_first_published: date experiment first published num_total_samples: total number samples experiment num_processed_samples: number samples experiment processed num_downloadable_samples: number samples experiment downloadable platform_names: names platforms used experiment organism_names: names organisms experiment sample_metadata_fields: types metadata available samples experiment samples: data.frame sample metadata

code: # this takes about 1-2 minutes to complete # for the entire experiment listing # depending on your internet connection # You only need to do this once (or when you want #   to update the results)  # get the first 2 pages of experiments for # testing and demonstration purposes experiments <- experiment_listing(.pages = 2) #> Error in experiment_listing(.pages = 2): could not find function "experiment_listing"  # get all experiments # experiments <- get_experiment_catalog()  head(experiments) #> Error in h(simpleError(msg, call)): error in evaluating the argument 'x' in selecting a method for function 'head': object 'experiments' not found dim(experiments) #> Error: object 'experiments' not found colnames(experiments) #> Error in h(simpleError(msg, call)): error in evaluating the argument 'x' in selecting a method for function 'colnames': object 'experiments' not found

title: Get one or more experiments (GSE, SRP, etc) from RefineBio — get_refinebio
text: quantile_normalize logical data quantile normalized? Default FALSE. TRUE, data quantile normalized based distribution data species. svd_algorithm character SVD algorithm use? One "NONE", "RANDOMIZED", "ARPACK" scale_by character scale data? One "NONE", "MINMAX", "STANDARD", "ROBUST" aggregate_by character aggregate data? One "EXPERIMENT", "SPECIES", "" experiment character() vector experiment IDs (e.g., GSE1133)s

text: Sean Davis <seandavi.gmail.com>

title: Get one or more experiments (GSE, SRP, etc) from RefineBio — get_refinebio
code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ # Get a single experiment expt <- get_refinebio("GSE116672")  # Get multiple experiments expts <- get_refinebio(c("SRP066613", "SRP158666"))  # Get multiple experiments with quantile normalization expts <- get_refinebio(   c("SRP066613", "SRP158666"),   quantile_normalize = TRUE ) # Get multiple experiments with quantile normalization and # aggregate everything into one summarized experiment expts <- get_refinebio(   c("SRP066613", "SRP158666"),   quantile_normalize = TRUE,   aggregate_by = "ALL" ) } # }
